'''百事可樂標誌'''（{{lang-en|Pepsi-Cola sign}}）是美國紐約市[[皇后區|皇后區]][[長島市|長島市]]{{tsl|en|Gantry Plaza State Park|龍門廣場州立公園}}（甘泉公園）內的[[霓虹燈|霓虹燈]]標誌牌，自[[曼哈頓|曼哈頓]]和[[東河_(紐約市)|東河]]均可望見。該標誌建於1940年，最初安裝在[[百事公司|百事公司]]的瓶裝廠上，由一個{{Convert|50|ft}}高的[[百事可樂|百事可樂]]瓶和百事可樂標誌（1906－1940年）字樣組成。

百事可樂的標誌字樣是由通用戶外廣告公司製作，在安裝後成為紐約州最長的電子標誌牌，而百事可樂瓶在1970年代被重新替換。1993年，{{tsl|en|Artkraft Strauss|Artkraft Strauss}}公司修復和重建已破損的百事可樂標誌，並於隔年重新安裝。2003年，百事可樂瓶裝廠關閉，該標誌被移往龍門廣場州立公園，而[[紐約市地標保護委員會|紐約市地標保護委員會]]則在1988年起多次舉辦聽證會，討論是否將該標誌作為城市地標，最終百事可樂標誌在2016年被指定為[[紐約市地標|紐約市地標]]。

== 設計 ==
原版的百事可樂標誌由通用戶外廣告公司（General Outdoor Advertising Corporation）製作，並安裝在位於第46大道和第5街的百事可樂瓶裝廠廠頂上<ref name="NYCL p. 7" />，面朝西方的曼哈頓[[聯合國總部大樓|聯合國總部]]。<ref name="Brill 2017">{{cite web|last=Brill|first=Louis M.|date=2006-02-20|title=The Pepsi-Cola Generation|url=https://www.signsofthetimes.com/content/the-pepsi-cola-generation|access-date=2020-07-30|website=Signs of the Times|language=en|archive-date=2020-09-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200907110829/https://www.signsofthetimes.com/content/the-pepsi-cola-generation|dead-url=no}}</ref>標誌牌字樣為{{Smallcaps|Pepsi:Cola 5c}}，尺寸為{{Convert|60|by|120|ft}}，旁邊裝有一個{{Convert|50|ft||abbr=|adj=on|sp=us}}長的百事可樂瓶。標誌中的{{Smallcaps|5c}}字樣為藍色，配有藍色[[霓虹燈|霓虹燈]]管，其餘字樣則為紅色，配有紅色霓虹燈管<ref name="bde19400829">{{cite news|date=1940-08-29|title=Pepsi-Cola Erects Huge Electric Sign|page=17|work=Brooklyn Daily Eagle|url=https://bklyn.newspapers.com/clip/56336813/|access-date=2020-07-29|via=Brooklyn Public Library；Newspapers.com™ {{open access}}|language=en|archive-date=2020-09-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200907110830/https://bklyn.newspapers.com/clip/56336813/pepsi-cola-erects-huge-electric-sign/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="nyt19400830">{{Cite news|date=1940-08-30|title=Advertising News and Notes; Resigns Jensen Account|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1940/08/30/archives/advertising-news-and-notes-resigns-jensen-account.html|access-date=2020-07-29|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2020-09-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200907110829/https://www.nytimes.com/1940/08/30/archives/advertising-news-and-notes-resigns-jensen-account.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="NYCL p. 4" />，而百事可樂瓶厚{{Convert|5|in}}<ref name="NYCL p. 7">{{harvnb|Landmarks Preservation Commission|2016|ps=.|p=7}}</ref>，由一對{{Convert|400|W|kW}}的燈管照明。<ref name="Brill 2017" />在標誌牌安裝的前一年，百事公司更改了標誌字樣，在其周圍塗上藍色輪廓，但可能是受百事可樂字樣使用紅色燈管的影響，標誌在1940年安裝時又取消了藍色輪廓。<ref name="NYCL p. 6" />

1993年，{{tsl|en|Artkraft Strauss|Artkraft Strauss}}公司重新設計了百事可樂標誌<ref name="nyt19940206">{{Cite news|last=Dunlap|first=David W.|date=1994-02-06|title=Signs Signal Both Profit and Controversy|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1994/02/06/realestate/signs-signal-both-profit-and-controversy.html|access-date=2020-07-29|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2020-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321183635/https://www.nytimes.com/1994/02/06/realestate/signs-signal-both-profit-and-controversy.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，同樣朝向西方的聯合國總部<ref name="LIC Post 2019">{{cite web|date=2019-08-21|title=JetBlue Logo Added to Pepsi Sign, Upsets Residents|url=https://licpost.com/jetblue-logo-added-to-pepsi-sign-upsets-residents|access-date=2020-07-30|author=Shane O'Brien|website=LIC Post|language=en|archive-date=2020-05-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200513014754/https://licpost.com/jetblue-logo-added-to-pepsi-sign-upsets-residents|dead-url=no}}</ref>，並安裝在長{{Convert|49|ft}}、寬{{Convert|150|ft}}的[[鋼|鋼]]架上，離地面至少{{Convert|20|ft}}高。標誌由[[鋁|鋁]]製的紅色{{Smallcaps|Pepsi:Cola}}字樣組成，邊緣裝有{{Convert|15|mm}}的霓虹燈管<ref name="NYCL p. 2">{{harvnb|Landmarks Preservation Commission|2016|ps=.|p=2}}</ref>，而「P」和「C」是其中最高的字母，高{{Convert|44|ft}}。<ref name="nyt20160412">{{Cite news|last=Dunlap|first=David W.|date=2016-04-12|title=Pepsi-Cola Sign in Queens Gains Landmark Status|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/04/13/nyregion/pepsi-cola-sign-in-queens-gains-landmark-status.html|access-date=2020-07-29|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2018-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181110082000/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/04/13/nyregion/pepsi-cola-sign-in-queens-gains-landmark-status.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>鋁製的百事可樂瓶位於字樣右側，高{{Convert|50|ft}}，亦裝有霓虹燈管，且依照1970年代的可樂瓶風格上漆繪製<ref name="NYCL p. 2" />，主要的區別是可樂瓶厚度因額外安裝一個電氣箱而被增加至{{Convert|9.5|in}}。<ref name="NYCL p. 7" />標誌牌的基座是由40根打入下層[[基岩|基岩]]的[[樁基|樁基]]所構成，每個樁基具有4個{{convert|5|ft|m}}的[[混凝土|混凝土]]樁帽。<ref name="NYCL p. 2" />

== 歷史 ==
[[長島市|長島市]]由於靠近曼哈頓和[[東河_(紐約市)|東河]]，因此在19世紀末及20世紀初發展成為商業和工業中心，百事可樂即是在長島市內發展的工廠之一。<ref name="NYCL p. 3">{{harvnb|Landmarks Preservation Commission|2016|ps=.|p=3}}</ref>1937年，該公司自[[美孚石油|美孚石油]]公司收購東河旁的三塊土地，以擴大其在[[皇后區|皇后區]]的業務，百事可樂也在此前於更內陸的第33街47－51號開設工廠。<ref name="NYCL p. 4">{{harvnb|Landmarks Preservation Commission|2016|ps=.|p=4}}</ref>

=== 原版標誌 ===
原版的百事可樂標誌於1940年8月30日被安裝在百事可樂長島市瓶裝廠的頂部<ref name="bde19400829" /><ref name="nyt19400830" />，成為瓶裝廠擴建的一部分<ref name="NYCL p. 4" />，在當時被宣傳為紐約州最長的電子標誌牌<ref name="nyt19400830" /><ref name="NYCL p. 4" />，同時正值長島市大量企業在樓頂安裝大型標誌牌的時期，曼哈頓、[[昆斯博羅橋|昆斯博羅橋]]、[[長島鐵路|長島鐵路]]或[[紐約地鐵|紐約地鐵]]高架線上均可看見。<ref name="NYCL pp. 5-6">{{harvnb|Landmarks Preservation Commission|2016|ps=.|pp=5–6}}</ref>文件顯示，{{tsl|en|New York City Department of Buildings|紐約市建築局}}於1940年5月批准該標誌的許可證。<ref name="NYCL p. 9">{{harvnb|Landmarks Preservation Commission|2016|ps=.|p=9}}</ref>而當時包括{{tsl|en|1916 Zoning Resolution|1916年都市規劃方案}}在內的城市法規禁止商業標誌出現在住宅區<ref>{{Cite news|last=Swan|first=Herbert S.|last2=Secretary|last3=Committee|first3=Zoning|date=1919-10-05|title=Zoning the Billboard|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1919/10/05/archives/zoning-the-billboard.html|access-date=2020-07-30|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2020-09-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200907110831/https://www.nytimes.com/1919/10/05/archives/zoning-the-billboard.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，後來又將標誌牌的表面積限制在{{Convert|500|ft2}}內、高度限制在[[路緣|路緣]]上方{{Convert|40|ft}}，該些規定嚴重影響大型標誌牌的設置。<ref name="NYCL p. 6">{{harvnb|Landmarks Preservation Commission|2016|ps=.|p=6}}</ref>

1940年代中葉，百事可樂的價格上漲，標誌牌上的5c字樣被移除，可樂瓶樣式也在1970年代被改為現代風格。<ref name="NYCL p. 6" />1990年代末，長島市[[水岸|水岸]]附近的工業逐漸遷往別處<ref name="NYCL p. 7" /><ref>{{Cite web|last=Fajardo|first=Sarah|date=2013-08-12|title=The History and Renewal of Long Island City and Dutch Kills, Queens|url=https://untappedcities.com/2013/08/12/history-renewal-long-island-city-dutch-kills-queens/|access-date=2020-07-30|website=Untapped New York|language=en-US|archive-date=2017-07-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170723122847/http://untappedcities.com/2013/08/12/history-renewal-long-island-city-dutch-kills-queens/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，該地區因成為{{tsl|en|Queens West|皇后西}}開發項目的一部分而進行規畫重建。<ref>{{Cite news|last=Gray|first=Christopher|date=1988-05-22|title=Streetscapes: Long Island City Power Station; A 1906 Railroad Landmark on the Queens Shoreline|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1988/05/22/realestate/streetscapes-long-island-city-power-station-1906-railroad-landmark-queens.html|dead-url=no|access-date=2020-07-30|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2020-08-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200831131434/https://www.nytimes.com/1988/05/22/realestate/streetscapes-long-island-city-power-station-1906-railroad-landmark-queens.html}}</ref>

[[紐約市地標保護委員會|紐約市地標保護委員會]]最初於1988年4月開始考慮是否將百事可樂標誌作為城市地標。<ref>{{cite news|date=1988-04-19|title=Tuesday Report|page=263|work=New York Daily News|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/56342112/|access-date=2020-07-29|via=Newspapers.com™ {{open access}}|language=en|archive-date=2020-09-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200907110859/https://www.newspapers.com/clip/56342112/tuesday-report/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="nyt19880418" />百事公司發言人表示，由於該標誌「幾乎就是個指標」，公司選擇以不更新標誌牌的方式反映出其現今的商標<ref name="nyt19880418">{{Cite news|last=Dunlap|first=David W.|date=1988-04-18|title=Landmarks Panel to Study Stable and Pepsi-Cola Sign|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1988/04/18/nyregion/landmarks-panel-to-study-stable-and-pepsi-cola-sign.html|access-date=2020-07-29|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2020-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321183633/https://www.nytimes.com/1988/04/18/nyregion/landmarks-panel-to-study-stable-and-pepsi-cola-sign.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>；時任皇后區{{tsl|en|Borough president|行政區長 (紐約市)|區長}}{{tsl|en|Claire Shulman|克萊爾·舒曼}}則以影響皇后西的發展為由，提議將該標誌移往他處，百事公司對此表達反對，並表示該公司擁有獨立控制標誌的權利。<ref>{{cite news|last=Leahy|first=Jack|date=1988-04-27|title=Claire fears 'Pepsi veneration'|page=585|work=New York Daily News|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/56342027/|access-date=2020-07-29|via=Newspapers.com™ {{open access}}|language=en|archive-date=2020-09-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200907110856/https://www.newspapers.com/clip/56342027/claire-fears-pepsi-veneration/|dead-url=no}}</ref>在討論該標誌地位的公聽會上，皇后區區長辦公室的兩位發言人均反對將其賦予城市地標的資格<ref name="NYCL p. 1">{{harvnb|Landmarks Preservation Commission|2016|ps=.|p=1}}</ref>，由於委員會成員對該提案缺乏興趣，因此紐約市地標保護委員會並未對此進行投票<ref name="nyt19940206" />，直至1990年代末，地標保護委員會都未曾將單獨的標誌指定為城市地標。<ref>{{Cite news|last=Weir|first=Richard|date=1998-08-09|title=Neighborhood Reports: Long Island City/Astoria; An Urban Beacon, the Swingline Sign May Outlast the Factory on Which It Stands|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1998/08/09/nyregion/neighborhood-reports-long-island-city-astoria-urban-beacon-swingline-sign-may.html|dead-url=no|access-date=2020-07-30|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2015-05-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150527080355/http://www.nytimes.com/1998/08/09/nyregion/neighborhood-reports-long-island-city-astoria-urban-beacon-swingline-sign-may.html}}</ref>

=== 重建和城市地標 ===
原版百事可樂標誌在{{tsl|en|December 1992 nor'easter|1992年12月東北風暴|1992年12月的東北風暴}}中幾乎被完全摧毀，整個標誌牌在1993年底被拆除，而{{tsl|en|Artkraft Strauss|Artkraft Strauss}}公司在其位於曼哈頓的工廠內重建了該標誌，字體樣式與原版相似。一位市政府發言人表示「改變這塊標誌就意味著其失去了一點紐約的質感」<ref name="nyt19940206" />，而由於紐約市地標保護委員會仍在考慮將百事可樂標誌指定為城市地標，因此重建的各個方面均需取得地標保護委員會批准。<ref name="NYCL p. 6" />2000年，百事公司宣布將撤走瓶裝廠，而皇后西、紐約市地標保護委員會及該公司在內均主張保留百事可樂標誌，之後地標保護委員會就是否保留該標誌再次舉辦聽證會。<ref>{{Cite news|last=Lippincott|first=E. E.|date=2000-11-05|title=Neighborhood Report: Long Island City; Pepsi, Too, Has a Classic, and It Will Stay On|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2000/11/05/nyregion/neighborhood-report-long-island-city-pepsi-too-has-a-classic-and-it-will-stay-on.html|dead-url=no|access-date=2020-07-29|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2018-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181129101923/https://www.nytimes.com/2000/11/05/nyregion/neighborhood-report-long-island-city-pepsi-too-has-a-classic-and-it-will-stay-on.html}}</ref>在百事公司將皇后區的業務全數轉移至{{tsl|en|College Point, Queens|學院角 (皇后區)|學院角}}後<ref>{{cite web|last=Dworkowitz|first=Alexander|date=2001-10-25|title=Pepsi to move LIC distribution to College Point|url=https://qns.com/story/2001/10/24/pepsi-to-move-lic-distribution-to-college-point/|access-date=2020-07-30|website=QNS.com|language=en|archive-date=2020-09-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200907110901/https://qns.com/story/2001/10/24/pepsi-to-move-lic-distribution-to-college-point/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，原本瓶裝廠的所在地隨即併入{{tsl|en|Gantry Plaza State Park|龍門廣場州立公園}}（甘泉公園）北部，成為該公園的一部分。<ref>{{cite news|last=Costella|first=AnnMarie|date=2009-07-09|title=Gantry Plaza Park Gains Six Acres|newspaper={{tsl|en|Queens Chronicle|皇后區紀事報|Queens Chronicle}}|url=https://www.qchron.com/editions/western/gantry-plaza-park-gains-six-acres/article_5f2a6db9-2e05-5f0d-8c5c-34993b652151.html|access-date=2020-07-29|language=en|archive-date=2020-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200118175047/https://www.qchron.com/editions/western/gantry-plaza-park-gains-six-acres/article_5f2a6db9-2e05-5f0d-8c5c-34993b652151.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Gray|first=Christopher|date=2004-11-07|title=On Waterfronts of the Present, Rail-Bridge Relics of the Past|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/11/07/realestate/on-waterfronts-of-the-present-railbridge-relics-of-the-past.html|access-date=2020-07-29|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2018-11-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181130031859/https://www.nytimes.com/2004/11/07/realestate/on-waterfronts-of-the-present-railbridge-relics-of-the-past.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

